To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, you can use the `\citealp` and `\citealp*` commands from the natbib package, or the `\footnote` command directly. Here's an example using the `\footnote` command:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{mciteplus}
\begin{document}
\title{Your Title}
\author{Author 1 \and Author 2 \and Author 3}
\date{}
\maketitle

\citealp{Author 1, Author 2, Author 3} contributed equally to this work.\mcitePlusAddHook{EndBibliography}{\citealp*{Author 1, Author 2, Author 3} contributed equally to this work.}

\end{document}
```

In this example, a footnote is added to the authors list indicating that all authors contributed equally to the work. The `\citealp` command is used to reference the authors in the text, and the `\citealp*` command is used to add the footnote. The `mcitePlusAddHook` command is used to add the footnote at the end of the bibliography.

